                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/133</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-20T08:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1916, 8 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A decree September 15 gives banks sixty days to cover their bills with metallic
                    reserves. Vera Cruz banks now closed. Decree sent by next mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
